The '''Display pixel interface''' ('''DPI''') is the interface defined by the [[Mobile Industry Processor Interface]] (MIPI), which is used for [[Active-matrix liquid crystal display|Active-Matrix LCD]] displays for [[handheld device]]s.  It is intended for the display modules in the mobile devices. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mipi.org/specifications|title=Specifications Overview - Display and Touch|last=|first=|date=|website=www.mipi.org|language=en|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-12-30}}</ref>

