{{Infobox dot-com company |name = Grok Learning |logo = Grok Learning logo.png |logo_size = 250px |company_type = Commercial |founded = 2013 |founder = Tara Murphy, [[James Curran (linguist)|James Curran]], Tim Dawborn, Nicky Ringland |location_city = [[Sydney]] |location_country = [[Australia]] |locations = |area_served = Worldwide |key_people = |industry = [[Internet industry|Internet]] |products = |services = [[Technology education]] |revenue = |operating_income = |net_income = |owner = |num_employees = 9 |parent = |divisions = |subsid = |url = {{URL|https://groklearning.com/|Grok Learning}} |ipv6 = |website_type = |advertising = |num_users = |language = |registration = |launch_date = |current_status = Active |commercial = Yes |screenshot = |caption = }} '''Grok Learning''' is an online interactive platform that offers coding classes in [[programming languages]] like [[Python (programming language)|Python]] and [[HTML]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://groklearning.com/ |title=Grok Learning |publisher=Grok Learning |date= |accessdate=2013-12-07}}</ref> Grok Learning has a focus on educating [[high school]] students, but also has content targeted specifically for professionals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://groklearning.com/professionals/ |title=Professional development |publisher=Grok Learning |date= |accessdate=2013-12-07}}</ref> Grok Learning provides courses suitable for use in a classroom setting where a computing trained teacher may or may not be present.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://groklearning.com/classroom/ |title=In the classroom |publisher=Grok Learning |date= |accessdate=2013-12-07}}</ref>
The site teaches students through a combination of notes and accompanying coding problems to solve. These problems can coded and run using the in-browser programming environment and are marked instantaneously by an auto-marker. The site offers feedback for solved problems, and badges for completing certain tasks, as well as leaderboards for certain courses. Grok has created a motto to encourage coders to keep going. This motto is "Grok On".
==History== Grok Learning was founded in 2013 by Tara Murphy, [[James Curran (linguist)|James Curran]], Tim Dawborn, and Nicky Ringland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://groklearning.com/about/ |title=Who are we? |publisher=Grok Learning |accessdate=2013-12-07}}</ref> At the time of foundation, James was an [[associate professor]] in the School of IT at [[The University of Sydney]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sydney.edu.au/it/~james/ |title=James Curran |publisher=James Curran |date= |accessdate=2013-12-07}}</ref> Tara was a [[senior lecturer]] in [[astroinformatics]] at [[The University of Sydney]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.physics.usyd.edu.au/~tara/ |title=Tara Murphy |publisher=Tara Murphy |date= |accessdate=2013-12-07}}</ref> and Tim and Nicky were [[computer science]] [[PhD candidate]]s at [[The University of Sydney]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sydney.edu.au/it/~tdaw3088/ |title=Tim Dawborn |publisher=Tim Dawborn |date= |accessdate=2013-12-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sydney.edu.au/it/~nicky/ |title=Nicky Ringland |publisher=Nicky Ringland |date= |accessdate=2013-12-07}}</ref> Since then, Tim and Nicky have completed their PhDs in 2015.
