'''Volume combustion synthesis''' (VCS) is method of [[chemical synthesis]] in which the [[reactant]]s are heated uniformly in a controlled manner until a reaction ignites throughout the volume of the reaction chamber.  The VCS mode is typically used for weakly exothermic reactions that require preheating prior to ignition.

